rComments: Prof. Gairdner is one of the best profs I've had at UofT. She brings in information from scholarly articles but combines it with her own personal experience. She encourages student discussion and opinions. Overall, very fair marker and genuinely has an interest in her students success. Also just a very easy to listen to lecturer. loved the course.
She's one of my favourite profs in kin! She really cares for her students and is easily approachable!
An open minded professor who cares about her students. If you work hard, you will get the grade you deserve! Solid choice!

rComments: Professor Gairdner definitely makes you work for it, but she was fantastic and super knowledgeable about many different topics. She is super down-to-earth, approachable and fair. She gives weekly quizzes on specific readings. She was definitely one of my favourite profs, although she is known to being a tough marker.
She is a caring professor. Solid choice, would recommend!
